{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stripe/stripe-python/pulls/1510", "id": 2496374116, "node_id": "PR_kwDOAB3Obc6Uy6Vk", "html_url": "https://github.com/stripe/stripe-python/pull/1510", "diff_url": "https://github.com/stripe/stripe-python/pull/1510.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/stripe/stripe-python/pull/1510.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/stripe/stripe-python/issues/1510", "number": 1510, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Require merge commit for merge PR (+ new rules.yml file) ", "user": {"login": "jar-stripe", "id": 179854761, "node_id": "U_kgDOCrhdqQ", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/179854761?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe", "html_url": "https://github.com/jar-stripe", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jar-stripe/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "### Why?\r\nOur merge script requires that PRs be merged with a merge commit to maintain git history and avoid conflicts in the future.  Our normal PR process is to squash before merging, usually with auto-merge enabled.  Since Github defaults to the last merge method selected, its very easy to accidentally enable auto-squash in this one situation where we really need a merge commit.\r\n\r\nNeither Github's branch rulesets nor branch protection rules let us define rules in the context of the HEAD ref, so this PR adds a CI that can.\r\n\r\n### What?\r\n- add rules.yml to define PR/branch rules that we cannot define in the Github UI\r\n- added Merge script PRs must create merge commits rule to run when auto merge is enabled and when the branch contains `/merge-`, and check that the auto merge method is 'merge'\r\n\r\n#### Demo\r\nWhen auto-merge is enabled on a merge PR like https://github.com/stripe/stripe-dotnet/pull/3106, it runs the rule as part of its checks.  If the auto-merge method is not 'merge', it fails:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7c5d3c91-1189-4e5f-94b1-e9c458f80e90)\r\n\r\nThe error provides a brief description about why it failed as a reminder to go fix the auto-merge method:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/47173537-8833-4795-8ccd-31234fa531f0)\r\n\r\nOnce fixed, the merge PR check is green, and everything's good to go:\r\n<img width=\"846\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eef640ec-91df-4d8a-9b86-fad0834c3738\" />\r\n\r\nNote that this must exist in the repo and enabled as a blocking status check to get the full benefit!\r\n\r\n### See Also\r\n<!-- Include any links or additional information that help explain this change. -->\r\n", "created_at": "2025-05-02T20:50:01Z", "updated_at": "2025-05-02T20:58:09Z", "closed_at": "2025-05-02T20:58:08Z", "merged_at": "2025-05-02T20:58:08Z", "merge_commit_sha": "9283e81a7b4b478fadd9adfca90ee1cc7dca7423", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [{"login": "mbroshi-stripe", "id": 94012587, "node_id": "U_kgDOBZqEqw", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/94012587?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mbroshi-stripe", "html_url": "https://github.com/mbroshi-stripe", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mbroshi-stripe/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mbroshi-stripe/following{/other_user}", "gists_url"